pdc_discovery.title: Possible caching issue when using widgets to filter

comments.body:
Unfortunately the issue is still showing up today: the search results (with no filter) show 246 or 364, which match the number of Solr documents in our two replicas:

```
curl 'localhost:9000/solr/pdc-discovery-production-2_shard1_replica_n1/select?q=*&rows=0'
# shows 246

curl 'localhost:9000/solr/pdc-discovery-production-2_shard1_replica_n2/select?q=*&rows=0'
# shows 364
```

These numbers match the discrepancy that we saw yesterday. It almost look like we are indexing differently the two replicas but I have no idea how that is happening. More to come.

Created a new Solr collection (`pdc-discovery-production-3`) with just one replica and reindexed to it. This new new collection has been aliased to `pdc-discovery-production` so it is now used by the system.

We'll need to verify tomorrow and eventually re-activate the replication. 

For details see section 4/11/2023 in this document: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YRBHCrDbU6tGQHE_ddH7Odha_Yy4SjgFenS_s6HtzyI/edit#heading=h.9rllnkg8fswz

rdss-catchall.title: Restoring files to Thesis-Central pre-04/10 database fix

comments.body:
Originally posted by James in #93 

Related to the service outage, an administrative user has provided the following error report from a user:

> An issue has come up with the files that were submitted prior to the site outage on Sunday. I received an error message when I try to view/download a file that was submitted earlier than 4/9.

 

> A student alerted me to the issue:

> 10:26

> Hello,I recently (on Saturday) uploaded my thesis onto Thesis Central. While everything on the site worked correctly then, today when I try to view the Manuscript in PDF of my thesis on the site an error occurs; in addition, when I view the submission of my thesis it now says the pdf has a size of 0 bytes. I just wanted to make you aware of the issue so that I can assure that my thesis is still properly stored on the site as it was on Saturday, especially considering that it is due today (Tuesday) at 4:30 PM.Thank you!

From James: 

The following postgreSQL query retrieves the paths and names for the files uploaded:

```bash
thesis-prod-db=> select a.name,a.data,sub.id from submission as sub inner join attachment as a on a.submission_id=sub.id inner join person as p on sub.submitter_id=p.id where email like '%[SUBMITTER_NAME]%';
```

rdss-catchall.title: thesis-central and thesis-central-qa are not accessible

comments.body:
I can confirm that I currently do have access to the new VMs `libtc203l` and `libtc103l` using the PuTTY on the bastion host `lib200w`. I am, however, limited in my user account privileges:

```bash
[libvijrg@libtc103l ~]$ sudo yum install tmux

We trust you have received the usual lecture from the local System
Administrator. It usually boils down to these three things:

    #1) Respect the privacy of others.
    #2) Think before you type.
    #3) With great power comes great responsibility.

Duo two-factor login for libvijrg

Enter a passcode or select one of the following options:

 1. Duo Push to XXX-XXX-8440
 2. Phone call to XXX-XXX-8440
 3. SMS passcodes to XXX-XXX-8440 (next code starts with: 2)

Passcode or option (1-3): 1

Pushed a login request to your device...
Success. Logging you in...
Sorry, user libvijrg is not allowed to execute '/usr/bin/yum install tmux' as root on libtc103l.aws.Princeton.EDU.
```
After attempting other possible approaches to elevating my privileges, I have explicitly requested the necessary privileges by e-mail.

Related to the service outage, an administrative user has provided the following error report from a user:

> An issue has come up with the files that were submitted prior to the site outage on Sunday. I received an error message when I try to view/download a file that was submitted earlier than 4/9.

 

> A student alerted me to the issue:

> 10:26

> Hello,I recently (on Saturday) uploaded my thesis onto Thesis Central. While everything on the site worked correctly then, today when I try to view the Manuscript in PDF of my thesis on the site an error occurs; in addition, when I view the submission of my thesis it now says the pdf has a size of 0 bytes. I just wanted to make you aware of the issue so that I can assure that my thesis is still properly stored on the site as it was on Saturday, especially considering that it is due today (Tuesday) at 4:30 PM.Thank you!

The following postgreSQL query retrieves the paths and names for the files uploaded:

```bash
thesis-prod-db=> select a.name,a.data,sub.id from submission as sub inner join attachment as a on a.submission_id=sub.id inner join person as p on sub.submitter_id=p.id where email like '%[SUBMITTER_NAME]%';
```

There clearly are files which were successfully uploaded throughout 04/10/23, I am still struggling to identify why there might be some which are missing:

```bash
[thesiscentralsu@libtc201l attachments]$ pwd
/home/thesiscentralsu/Vireo/data/attachments
[thesiscentralsu@libtc201l attachments]$ find . -type f -exec ls -l {} \;
-rw-r--r-- 1 thesiscentralsu thesiscentralsu 395858 Apr 10 11:54 ./aa/ec/00/0f/aaec000f-1641-4703-9f2d-1283bbb06c63
-rw-r--r-- 1 thesiscentralsu thesiscentralsu 2343669 Apr 10 23:05 ./aa/a2/6f/b7/aaa26fb7-1a31-4b0d-887a-e3e4b0cacce8
-rw-r--r-- 1 thesiscentralsu thesiscentralsu 248 Apr 10 13:29 ./94/42/72/0d/9442720d-202a-451f-bd89-3c7371c92ede
-rw-r--r-- 1 thesiscentralsu thesiscentralsu 250 Apr 10 15:53 ./32/41/83/76/32418376-5c42-42c6-a863-a16edb2b4c4e
-rw-r--r-- 1 thesiscentralsu thesiscentralsu 1622191 Apr 10 11:40 ./32/41/b7/49/3241b749-a356-4368-93d2-6ec92d6129da
```
Increasing the points on this one to account for the fact that 6+ people spent much of a day on restoring missing PDFs.

While this session is still in progress, it should be noted that there were a number of PDF files which were deleted during the troubleshooting for the application. In response to this, OIT has, fortunately, provided snapshots for the file system for the EC2 instances.
Run book for restore process - https://docs.google.com/document/d/17dXwE9EN9GbAq7gBpQ6SgEAs4wmHs6KytCDXJZ6Q5vg/edit

Currently, I am blocked from transferring the database export file from the production application server into the new QA database server environment, likely by firewall restrictions. I have issued a request for support in order to advance this:

> I am sorry for continuing this thread, however, I have reached a point at which I have deployed the postgresql server on libtc103l (for the new QA database), and I am currently trying to migrate the database export from the current production server (libtc201l for the production application). Unfortunately, I do not believe that I can achieve this over the network due to firewall restrictions.

> postgres@libtc201l$ psql -h libtc103l.aws.princeton.edu -W -U thesis-qa thesis-qa-db <  thesis_prod_db_04_11_23b.sql

> Might this be possible to please request? Otherwise, might there be some other means to transfer the database export file from libtc201l to libtc103l?

Following a pairing session between @kayiwa and I, a database export from a snapshot of the current production server (libtc201l) has been successfully imported into the new PostgreSQL database server for the QA environments (libtc103l).

While there are still questions and concerns regarding how best to manage the database backup exports and restoring these backups, please know that that, once this is determined, the path for upgrading the production server environment with the new database server (libtc203l) shall be fully identified.
Superseded by #29.
